Enum VariableEliminator.VariableCost

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<VariableEliminator.VariableCost>
      • com.analog.lyric.dimple.model.transform.VariableEliminator.VariableCost
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<VariableEliminator.VariableCost>
    Enclosing class:
    VariableEliminator

    public static enum VariableEliminator.VariableCost
extends java.lang.Enum<VariableEliminator.VariableCost>
    Describes the standard built-in variable cost functions supported by VariableEliminator. See members for details.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      MIN_FILL
      Cost is the number of edges that would be introduced between neighboring variables if this variable were to be eliminated at this step.
      MIN_NEIGHBORS
      Cost is the number of neighboring variables that have not yet been eliminated.
      WEIGHTED_MIN_FILL
      Cost is the sum of the weights of the edges that would be introduced between neighboring variables if this variable were to be eliminated at this step, where the edge weights are the products of the domain cardinalities of the variables connected by the edge.
      WEIGHTED_MIN_NEIGHBORS
      Cost is the product of the domain cardinalities of the neighboring variables that have not yet been eliminated.
